---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use | Cognit System"
  description="The terms that apply when you use the Cognit System website, cognitsystem.com — a product of Zeabyte Limited. Plain-English website terms covering use, content, intellectual property and liability."
  path="/terms"
>
  <Header />

  <main class="bg-cog-stone text-cog-slate">
    <!-- HERO (photographic) -->
    <section class="orbs relative isolate overflow-hidden">
      <img src="/images/hero-port-night.jpg" alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 h-full w-full object-cover" />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-cog-ink/82"></div>
      <div class="dotgrid absolute inset-0 -z-10 opacity-40"></div>
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 pt-20 pb-20 text-center sm:px-8 sm:pt-28 hero-rise">
        <span class="chip mx-auto border border-white/15 text-slate-200">
          <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-cog-teal"></span> The fine print, in plain English
        </span>
        <h1 class="mx-auto mt-7 max-w-3xl text-[2.6rem] font-extrabold leading-[1.05] tracking-tight text-white sm:text-6xl">
          Terms of <span class="text-gradient-bright">Use</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
          The terms that apply when you use this website. We've kept them clear and to
          the point.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BODY -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-20 sm:px-8">
      <article class="article">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-cog-slate/70">Last updated: 20 June 2026</p>

        <p>
          These Terms of Use apply to your use of this website,
          <strong>cognitsystem.com</strong> (the "site"), operated by
          <strong>Cognit System</strong>, a product of <strong>Zeabyte Limited</strong>
          (NZBN 9429052028748). By using the site, you agree to these terms.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Acceptance of these terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using this site you accept these Terms of Use. If you don't
          agree with them, please don't use the site. We may update these terms from time
          to time, and the version published here is the one that applies.
        </p>

        <h2>2. The site is informational</h2>
        <p>
          This site exists to tell you about Cognit and to let you get in touch with us.
          The information on it is provided for general guidance only and may be updated or
          changed at any time. It isn't a contract, an offer of service, or professional
          advice, and using a product or service is subject to a separate written
          agreement with us.
        </p>

        <h2>3. No warranty</h2>
        <p>
          We work hard to keep the information on this site accurate and up to date, but we
          provide it "as is" and "as available", without warranties of any kind. We don't
          guarantee that the site will always be available, error-free or uninterrupted, or
          that the information on it is complete or current.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          All content on this site — including text, graphics, logos, images, layout and
          design — is owned by or licensed to Zeabyte Limited and is protected by
          intellectual property laws. "Cognit", "Cognit System", "Zeabyte" and related
          names and marks belong to Zeabyte Limited. You may view and share the site for
          your own information, but you may not copy, reproduce, republish or use our
          content or marks for any other purpose without our written permission.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Pricing</h2>
        <p>
          Any prices shown on this site are indicative, in New Zealand dollars, and may
          change at any time without notice. Final pricing is confirmed in a written quote
          or agreement tailored to your business. Nothing on this site is a binding offer
